Viktor Alksnis, former USSR Supreme Soviet deputy,

[Correspondent Irina Zaytseva] Viktor Alksnis, born 1950, Latvian, former deputy of the Supreme Soviet of the former USSR, soldier, resigned from the Army in order to fight for the restoration of the USSR.
[end recording] [Zaytseva] Apart from that, Alksnis added, according to information received from reliable sources, certain circles in Moscow want conflict in Latvia.
[Begin Alksnis recording] You understand that I cannot name these sources.
[end recording] [Zaytseva] Asked what he intends to do, Alksnis said his opportunities are unfortunately limited, and that is why he is appealing to journalists.
